:left"><b><strong>How to Find the Covariance Matrix?</strong></b></h2><p di=
r=3D"ltr"><span>The dimensions of a covariance matrix are determined by the=
 number of variables in a given data set. If there are only two variables i=
n a set, then the covariance matrix would have two rows and two columns. Si=
milarly, if a data set has three variables, then its covariance matrix woul=
d have three rows and three columns.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=3D"ltr"><span>T=
he data pertains to the marks scored by Anna, Caroline, and Laura in Psycho=
logy and History. Make a covariance matrix.</span></p><table><thead><tr><th=
 style=3D"text-align: center;"><b><strong>Student</strong></b></th><th styl=
