p dir=3D"ltr"><b><strong>Step 8:&nbsp;</strong></b><span>Repeat the same fo=
r variable Y; (70 - 47), (20 - 47), (50 - 47).</span></p><p dir=3D"ltr"><b>=
<strong>Step 9:&nbsp;</strong></b><span>Multiply the corresponding terms: (=
80 - 81)(70 - 47), (63 - 81)(20 - 47), (100 - 81)(50 - 47).</span></p><p di=
r=3D"ltr"><b><strong>Step 10:&nbsp;</strong></b><span>Find the covariance b=
